  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <details><summary>Which protocol is best for speed?</summary><p>WireGuard (or NordLynx) is typically the fastest while remaining secure.</p></details>
  <details><summary>Should I change encryption for more speed?</summary><p>No. Keep AES-256-GCM or ChaCha20-Poly1305. Downgrading encryption risks privacy for minimal gains.</p></details>
  <details><summary>Do I need a kill switch?</summary><p>Yes. A <a href="/en-us/blog/vpn-kill-switch.html">kill switch</a> prevents IP exposure if the VPN drops.</p></details>
  <details><summary>What about DNS?</summary><p>Use your provider’s encrypted DNS to avoid <a href="/en-us/blog/vpn-dns-leak.html">DNS leaks</a>.</p></details>

